      "content": "Those suggestions for the models sound good, but I'm more worried about the human evaluation part. The reviewers are definitely going to ask about the human participant pool for the psychometric side.\n\nSince we're aiming for Nature, how should we describe the participant sample in the abstract? I want to make sure it sounds substantial and statistically significant so they don't think the findings are just based on a small, unrepresentative group.",
